Jeanette Chabalala, News24(File) (Nielen de Klerk, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg &ndash; Five people were killed and several injured when two suspected robbers crashed into a minibus on the N3 north, near Alberton, on Monday, Gauteng police said.Police were chasing two suspects who were allegedly linked to violent crimes and a shoot-out ensued, Lieutenant Colonel Lungelo Dlamini told News24. &nbsp;&ldquo;The suspected robbers crashed into a minibus taxi, which resulted in five people losing their lives. Several people were transported to hospital for further medical attention,&rdquo; he said. &nbsp; &nbsp; &ldquo;Two guns were found in the suspects' abandoned car. One of them is believed to have been shot." &nbsp;&nbsp; The two ran away and were still at large.The accident caused traffic congestion between the Elands and Geldenhuys interchanges between 14:00 and 16:00, Ekurhuleni metro police spokesperson Lieutenant Colonel Wilfred Kgasago said.&nbsp; 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.